 by the county council, mainly health care and public transport. Like other counties, Gotland has a County Administrative Board that oversees implementation of the Swedish state government. Both the County Administrative Board and the municipality have their seat in the largest city Visby, with over 22,000 inhabitants.", "qas": [{"question": "what is the county or `` l\u00e4n '' ?", "answers": [], "id": "(34, 0, 0)"}]}, {"context": "The provinces of Sweden are no longer officially administrative units, but are used when reporting population size, politics, etc. In this case the province, the county and the municipality all have identical borders and cover an area of 3151\u00a0km\u00b2 (3151\u00a0km\u00b2 when excluding the lakes and rivers).", "qas": []}, {"context": "Gotland is the only Swedish county that is not administered by a county council. Instead, the municipality is tasked with the responsibilities of a county, including public health care and public transport.", "qas": [{"question": "which county is the only one that is not administered by a county council ?", "answers": [], "id": "(34, 2, 0)"}]}, {"context": "The main aim of the County Administrative Board is to fulfil the goals set in national politics by the Riksdag and the Government, to coordinate the interests and promote the development of the county, to establish regional goals and safeguard the due process of law in the handling of each case. The County Administrative Board is a Government agency headed by a Governor.", "qas": []}, {"context": "During a trial period the County Council provisions for Gotland has been evolved to provisions for a Regional Council, meaning that it has assumed certain tasks from the County Administrative Board. Similar provisions are applicable to the counties of V\u00e4stra G\u00f6taland and Sk\u00e5ne during the trial period.", "qas": []}, {"context": "The five most populous localities of Gotland County in 2010:", "qas": []}, {"context": "Gotland County inherited it